EACC deputy chief executive officer Michael Mubea has urged the Kilifi executive committee to swiftly prepare a plan to implement its corruption risk assessment report.He gave them one month.Mubea said this on Thursday, when he presented the report to Governor Amason Kingi.&ldquo;There is need for the county executive to design appropriate governance and operational instruments as a matter of priority. These should include policies, manuals and operational guidelines to guide activities in all functions,&rdquo; he said.Mubea told Kingi to ensure compliance .He said the commission will monitor and establish whether the officers comply with the law and regulations that guide purchase of goods and services. Kingi said he is committed to working closely with the EACC.